<subSubSection id="C304652A4D21324CFF274503FE2332BE" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D21324CFF274503FE2332BE" blockId="3.[151,1437,1734,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D21324CFF274503FEE43277" bold="true" box="[199,314,1878,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D21324CFEA84502FE013277" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" box="[328,479,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Cladocalon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D21324CFEA84502FE013277" box="[328,479,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated by the elongate yellow stripe at elytra basal third or half, branch of the third antennomere slightly longer than twice of antennomere, and male genitalia with single-hooked parameres followed by short median hook.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
