<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF27433BFC0434AA" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FF27433BFE8C348F" bold="true" box="[199,338,366,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B504D243249FEB7433AFDDD348E" author="Gorham, H. S." box="[343,515,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" pagination="225 - 272" refId="ref5500" refString="Gorham, H. S. (1884) Malacodermata. Fam. Lycidae. Biologia Centrali-Americana, 3 (2), Supplement, 225 - 272." type="journal article" year="1884">Gorham (1884)</bibRefCitation>
considered individuals of this new species as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB9F433AFA48348E" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1151,1430,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Calocladon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrionicum">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB9F433AFA48348E" box="[1151,1430,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Calocladon histrionicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based mostly on color pattern but presenting longer humeral yellow stripe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
